hopobject.body: Do you need a work permit? croydon pharmacy 24 hour Human Rights Watch is accusing opposition forces in Syria fighting to defeat the Assad regime of committing crimes against humanity. The New York headquartered charity says it has documented at least 190 cases of civilians being killed by Islamist rebels on 4 August. Sixty-seven of them, it said, were executed during an offensive on ten villages in Latakia province, cradle of Syria’s Alawite minority, to which the clan of President Bashar al-Assad belongs.
